         ENTERED=20011114
         UPDATED=20011119
           SHORT="GGv is the GNOME PDF and PostScript viewer program"
cat << EOF
GGv is the GNOME PDF and PostScript viewer program.

GGv allows you to view, print, zoom, and isolate pages from PDF and
PostScript document files. GGv's main features are antialiasing, 
drag-and-drop capability for loading files, easy document navigation, and
transparent compressed document support.

The name comes from Ghostview, a non-gnome GNU PostScript viewer
application on which GGv is based.

GGv uses Ghostscript to do the actual interpretting and displaying of
PostScript and PDF documents. GGv provides an easy-to-use interface to
that program.
EOF
